{
  "texts": [
    "The Peruvians were very nasty about it, gave a huge fine and said they needed three million dollars to let Onassis's fleet go again.",
    "We believed we had killed the monster the night that this happened.",
    "Much to our amazement, we saw and learned that he had anticipated the whole thing by booking for disasters at Lloyd's of London.",
    "So, all in all, we watched him make a profit.",
    "He got 15 million dollars in insurance money and three thousand each day that he was out of the whaling operation."
  ]
}